cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving language models, which is a core topic in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes improvements to the RNN structure, which is a common model used in machine learning. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions experiments on language modeling and classification tasks, which are common tasks in NLP and machine learning. This makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions using feature hashing, which is a common technique in computer vision. This makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
